                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.34/259</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>)<note n="57" xml:id="d68fn57"
                        >Submitted by the Under Secretary of State to the Secretary of State on May
                        17</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-17">May 17,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dr. Sao-Ke Alfred Sze, Acting Chairman of China Defense Supplies, Inc., called
                    upon me today at his request, to inform me that he had had a conference this
                    morning with the Secretary of the Navy relative to the matter of the United
                    States Navy turning over to the Chinese Government, under Lend-Lease, four
                    destroyers of approximately fifteen hundred tons each, and four mine layers of
                    about one thousand tons each.</p>
                <p>The plan is for the ships to fly the Chinese flag, to have Chinese crews, and to
                    represent the foundation of the Chinese Navy.</p>
                <p>Dr. Sze stated that Mr. Forrestal had promised to review the matter promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
